verbose_text: High concentrations of reactive oxygen species (ROS) cause lipid peroxidation and damage to cell membranes, proteins and mitochondrial DNA, which exacerbates mitochondrial dysfunction, reduces mitochondrial energy production and triggers apoptotic cell death through the activation of the caspase-3 pathway.
